      "module_path": "track",
      "docs": "Typed input for the track command family. The first 14 variants (Init through DetectActive) are unchanged from the pre-existing declaration authored in track/items/cli-layers-tddd-and-role-placement-lint-2026-06-24/cli_driver-types.json and are reproduced verbatim here since action=modify requires a complete post-modification declaration, not a partial diff — except that every PathBuf-typed field (items_dir / project_root, one per pre-existing variant) is spelled out as the full std::path::PathBuf path rather than the source entry's bare PathBuf: that source entry carried action=reference, under which Phase 2 does not structurally compare field content, so the bare spelling was harmless there, but this entry's action=modify does undergo structural comparison against current rustdoc, and PathBuf is absent from the A-codec's auto-resolve set (libs/infrastructure/src/tddd/type_ref_parser/constants.rs: PRIMITIVE_TYPES / STD_PRELUDE_TYPES), so a bare PathBuf would misresolve as an in-crate type and mismatch. This track adds a 15th variant, CatalogueLintCheckActiveTrack, carrying the `sotp catalogue-lint check-active-track` request through TrackDriver::handle to TrackService::catalogue_lint_check_active_track — correcting a CLI-boundary violation where cli called TrackCompositionRoot::catalogue_lint_check_active_track directly, bypassing this driver (CN-01/CN-02: cli must not call cli_composition workflow methods directly). TrackDriver itself needs no catalogue change: its handle(&self, input: TrackInput) -> CommandOutcome signature is unchanged; only its match-arm body gained a case for the new variant. R9 note: track_id / workspace_root / rules_file remain raw Option<String> / std::path::PathBuf / Option<std::path::PathBuf> rather than dedicated value objects — this mirrors the exact primitive types already used by all 14 pre-existing variants on this enum (track_id: Option<String>/String throughout; PathBuf-typed items_dir/project_root throughout) and by the already-written, catalogue-only-task-out-of-scope Rust enum variant this entry documents; introducing e.g. a TrackId/WorkspaceRoot newtype here would diverge from the compiled enum signature (Phase 2 mismatch) and would require a Rust source change outside this task's authorized scope. Flagged for a possible future R9 follow-up pass across the whole TrackInput surface, not resolved by this track.",
